                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Lic. <hi rend="superscript"
                        >Douglas/52</hi> Aircraft Co. Inc./5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-30T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 30, 1938—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>454. Your no. 991, June 28, 5 p.m. The laws prohibiting the exportation of arms
                    to Spain contain no provisions under which exceptions to the prohibition could
                    be granted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
